# Personal adaptive touch model (PLAN.md "Touch decoding", stage 2).
#
# PERSONAL_TOUCH seeds per-key Welford aggregates (count, mean offset,
# sigmas, covariance) exactly as the extension would extract them from
# personal-model.json; the engine prices tapped substitutions against the
# shrinkage-blended personal Gaussian once a key clears the min-samples
# gate (EngineConfig.touchPersonalMinSamples = 30, prior strength k = 50).
# All runs use the REAL artifacts — every flip below is a ranking the
# TSI-seeded static prior does NOT produce (the stage-1 twins of these
# scenarios live in core.scenarios: "tap direction disambiguates hestir",
# "dead-center taps demote the substitution readings of hestir",
# "dead-center taps veto the koetip auto-apply").

SCENARIO below-gate touch stats keep the static ranking
# 20 effective samples < the 30-sample gate: the personal mean must not
# participate — same bar as the tapless-prior core scenario (hesti leads,
# hestur priced out of the bar by the dead-center taps).
PERSONAL_TOUCH u 20 0.45 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP h 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP s 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hesti
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS hestur
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO habitual right-edge u tapper resurrects hestur from dead-center taps
# The user's u taps center 0.45 key pitches RIGHT (toward i) with prior-
# shaped spread, 500 effective samples → blended personal u sits ~0.41
# toward the i key. A dead-center i tap — which the static prior reads as
# "definitely i", demoting every substitution — is now a plausible u for
# THIS user: the hestur (i→u) reading cheapens from the ~7-nat static
# exponent to ~2.4 nats and retakes the top of the bar. hestir is BÍN-
# valid, so ranking only — nothing may auto-apply.
PERSONAL_TOUCH u 500 0.45 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP h 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP s 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hestur
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO gair static baseline for the personal flip
# All-dead-center taps: both 1-sub readings (hair g→h, fair g→f) price
# near the full-pitch exponent, so the extra-character reading "air"
# (flat 4-nat indel — taps cannot reprice indels) leads. Margin-tied
# tail, nothing auto-applies.
TAP g 0 0
TAP a 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP air
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO habitual left-edge h tapper flips gair to hair
# Same taps, same word. This user's h taps center 0.45 key pitches LEFT
# (toward g): the dead-center g tap lands well inside their personal h
# cloud, the hair reading undercuts the 4-nat indel, and the top of the
# bar flips air → hair — a ranking the static prior cannot produce from
# these coordinates.
PERSONAL_TOUCH h 500 -0.45 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP g 0 0
TAP a 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hair
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO corrupt touch stats fall back to the static prior
# A NaN mean (corrupt model file) must drop the key to the prior, not
# poison pricing: identical bar to the below-gate scenario.
PERSONAL_TOUCH u 500 nan 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP h 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP s 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hesti
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS hestur
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO neutral personal stats leave the dead-center koetip veto intact
# Personal data whose blend ~reproduces the prior (zero mean, TSI sigmas)
# must not weaken the stage-1 correction veto: dead-center koetip taps
# still say "believe the user".
PERSONAL_TOUCH e 500 0.0 0.0 0.263 0.188
PERSONAL_TOUCH p 500 0.0 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS kortið
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "koetip "

SCENARIO neutral personal stats keep the boundary-tap koetip repair firing
# And the ENABLING half survives too: the same neutral personal stats,
# boundary taps toward the keys kortið needs — the repair fires exactly
# like the static engine.
PERSONAL_TOUCH e 500 0.0 0.0 0.263 0.188
PERSONAL_TOUCH p 500 0.0 0.0 0.263 0.188
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0.45 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0.45 0
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT kortið
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "kortið "
